A general web designing course syllabus can be simply classified into the major concepts of web designing and programming languages as well as the tools and software required for designing web pages. Here are the important topics covered in Web Designing Syllabus:

    Basics of Web Designing
    Multimedia and its Applications
    Web Technologies
    Introduction to Web Design & Applications
    Computer Graphics
    Mathematical Structure for Computer Science
    HTML
    CSS
    JavaScript
    Bootstrap
    Adobe Dreamweaver
    Adobe Flash
    Available Softwares for Graphic Designing
    Animation Techniques
